    "body": "Adds PrecisionConfig.intermediate_out_dtype so split-K matmul can store intermediate scratch outputs in a configurable dtype, defaulting to the existing fp32 behavior. Also threads the dtype through split-K allocation and opt-flag shared-memory sizing, with tests covering bf16 scratch allocation and dtype normalization.",
